    "methodology": "Alcohol-specific deaths are those caused by conditions wholly attributable to alcohol, classified using ICD-10 codes. The ONS definition includes alcoholic liver disease, mental and behavioural disorders due to alcohol, and accidental poisoning by alcohol. Hospital admissions data covers all episodes where an alcohol-related condition was the primary or secondary diagnosis. Liver disease mortality is a subset of alcohol-specific deaths where alcoholic liver disease (K70) was the underlying cause.",
    "knownIssues": [
      "COVID-19 pandemic disrupted both drinking patterns and healthcare access in 2020-2021, creating a step change in the data",
      "Hospital admissions figures for 2020 are artificially suppressed due to reduced healthcare access during lockdowns",
